German Rider Tony Martin Wins Paris-Nice Race, Kloden Second, AFP Reports

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-03-13T15:34:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-13/german-rider-tony-martin-wins-paris-nice-race-kloden-second-afp-reports.html
  Germany ’s Tony Martin, of the HTC-
Highroad team, won the Paris-Nice bike race as French champion
Thomas Voeckler of Europcar took the eighth and final stage
today,  Agence France-Presse  reported.  Martin came 16th in today’s stage, raced over 77 miles
around Nice.  German rider Andreas Kloden, of the RadioShack team, was
second overall, provisionally timed at 36 seconds behind Martin.
Britain’s Bradley Wiggins, of Sky, was five seconds further
back.           To contact the editor responsible for this story:
